WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:02.044 --> 00:00:03.212
[car horns honking]

2
00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:06.131
[helicopter whirring]

3
00:00:12.429 --> 00:00:14.306
{\an8}[news reporter] <i>From our
eye in the sky we are seeing</i>

4
00:00:14.389 --> 00:00:17.643
{\an8}<i>unprecedented traffic
chaos across the capital.</i>

5
00:00:17.726 --> 00:00:21.147
{\an8}<i>According to eyewitnesses.
several cars ground to a halt.</i>

6
00:00:21.230 --> 00:00:23.899
{\an8}<i>their engines
bursting into flames.</i>

7
00:00:23.982 --> 00:00:27.361
{\an8}<i>Injuries are reported
but no fatalities as yet.</i>

8
00:00:27.444 --> 00:00:31.282
{\an8}<i>The areas around the vehicles
are experiencing severe gridlock</i>

9
00:00:31.365 --> 00:00:34.493
{\an8}<i>which is hampering the
response of emergency services.</i>

10
00:00:34.576 --> 00:00:36.495
{\an8}<i>There is no word on
what caused this.</i>

11
00:00:42.626 --> 00:00:45.129
Take Ho down to
interrogation cell eight.

12
00:00:45.212 --> 00:00:46.797
-The fright cube?
-Yep.

13
00:00:48.632 --> 00:00:51.218
I know my rights. I need
to talk to my dad's lawyer.

14
00:00:51.301 --> 00:00:53.011
You don't get any phone calls.

15
00:00:54.263 --> 00:00:57.099
And if you did. you're better
off calling the dry cleaner

16
00:00:57.683 --> 00:00:58.684
and a dentist.

17
00:01:02.896 --> 00:01:06.442
Why am I getting my updates
on burning cars from the news?

18
00:01:06.525 --> 00:01:07.526
Apologies. ma'am.

19
00:01:07.609 --> 00:01:09.570
We've been waiting until we
know for sure what happened.

20
00:01:09.653 --> 00:01:11.572
-And do you?
-Well. we've ruled out terror.

21
00:01:11.655 --> 00:01:12.948
They weren't car bombs.

22
00:01:13.031 --> 00:01:15.910
It seems a chemical in the fuel caused
the engines to seize up and overheat.

23
00:01:15.993 --> 00:01:17.620
And what are the fuel
companies saying?

24
00:01:17.703 --> 00:01:19.788
Denying liability.
Claiming sabotage.

25
00:01:20.372 --> 00:01:23.083
First Desk is looking into how and
where it might have taken place.

26
00:01:23.166 --> 00:01:24.418
Oh. is he?

27
00:01:24.501 --> 00:01:26.211
I don't understand. um...

28
00:01:26.712 --> 00:01:29.131
Why are there still all these
burning cars on the roads?

29
00:01:29.715 --> 00:01:31.926
Uh. the police can't move
them until the flames are out

30
00:01:32.009 --> 00:01:34.970
and the firefighters can't get in
there until the gridlock eases.

31
00:01:35.596 --> 00:01:36.931
-Yeah. but then...
-[phone buzzing]

32
00:01:37.014 --> 00:01:38.473
Oh. excuse me. Sorry.

33
00:01:39.933 --> 00:01:40.934
[mumbles]

34
00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:42.978
[clears throat]

35
00:01:45.731 --> 00:01:46.649
Whelan.

36
00:01:46.732 --> 00:01:48.108
[Carl] <i>We met on your jog.</i>

37
00:01:49.943 --> 00:01:51.737
<i>Do you have an official
comment on the story</i>

38
00:01:51.820 --> 00:01:54.490
<i>we're going to run for
Dodie Gimball's column?</i>

39
00:01:54.573 --> 00:01:57.910
You shouldn't have this
phone number. How dare you?

40
00:01:59.286 --> 00:02:01.497
There will be repercussions.
I promise you that.

41
00:02:01.580 --> 00:02:03.582
[Carl] <i>The repercussions
are on you.</i>

42
00:02:03.665 --> 00:02:05.501
<i>If you weren't so
busy chasing skirt</i>

43
00:02:05.584 --> 00:02:08.044
<i>maybe we wouldn't have
shootings and gridlock.</i>

44
00:02:08.878 --> 00:02:11.590
-[stammers]
-Is this traffic situation contained?

45
00:02:12.883 --> 00:02:15.719
Uh. yeah. um. about
ten minutes ago.

46
00:02:15.802 --> 00:02:17.680
I was about to shut down
every gas station in London.

47
00:02:17.763 --> 00:02:19.306
-Petrol station.
-Petrol... petrol station.

48
00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:22.101
Thankfully we established
that all the affected stations

49
00:02:22.184 --> 00:02:23.936
had a delivery from
one single tanker.

50
00:02:24.019 --> 00:02:26.439
So. traffic should be back to
normal by the end of the day.

51
00:02:26.522 --> 00:02:28.399
The fence at the depot was cut.

52
00:02:28.482 --> 00:02:30.693
so we're assuming that's
where the tampering happened.

53
00:02:30.776 --> 00:02:32.445
Likely by climate protestors.

54
00:02:32.528 --> 00:02:34.989
[news reporter] <i>Our
London mayor Zafar Jaffrey</i>

55
00:02:35.072 --> 00:02:37.533
<i>has issued a statement
calling for calm</i>

56
00:02:37.616 --> 00:02:42.288
<i>in the wake of what sources are saying
is the result of fuel tampering.</i>

57
00:02:42.371 --> 00:02:45.166
[Zafar] <i>While the emergency services
are doing everything they can</i>

58
00:02:45.249 --> 00:02:48.544
<i>to get the roads clear. I would
urge people to leave their cars...</i>

59
00:02:48.627 --> 00:02:51.347
[person. in Arabic] Look at them
down there. we've driven them crazy.

60
00:02:52.130 --> 00:02:54.425
And what's coming next will
drive them even crazier.

61
00:02:54.508 --> 00:02:56.301
[news reporter
continues on radio]

62
00:02:58.303 --> 00:02:59.304
[sniffs]

63
00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:07.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

64
00:03:08.897 --> 00:03:10.482
How many will it kill?

65
00:03:10.899 --> 00:03:13.485
All of them. It
will be a massacre.

66
00:03:16.154 --> 00:03:19.157
["Strange Game" playing]

67
00:04:01.200 --> 00:04:02.367
[car horns honking]

68
00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.624
[Flyte] The gridlock is focused
mainly around those vehicles.

69
00:04:08.707 --> 00:04:11.793
so Muswell Hill. Elephant and
Castle. Mile End. and the City.

70
00:04:14.004 --> 00:04:17.548
No fatalities. Although. there
is a pensioner in intensive care.

71
00:04:20.844 --> 00:04:23.305
Sorry. why has the explosives
unit been stood down?

72
00:04:24.723 --> 00:04:27.476
Well. that would've been
nice to know. [scoffs]

73
00:04:29.853 --> 00:04:32.064
So why did the
engines explode then?

74
00:04:35.526 --> 00:04:37.778
Well. once the fire is
out. get forensics in.

75
00:04:37.861 --> 00:04:39.613
They should be able to tell
us what the chemical was

76
00:04:39.696 --> 00:04:41.782
-and where it came from.
-What's the plan?

77
00:04:41.865 --> 00:04:43.367
[Flyte] Doesn't help
that I'm stuck over here.

78
00:04:43.450 --> 00:04:44.535
The usual.

79
00:04:45.994 --> 00:04:46.995
So. do nothing?

80
00:04:47.496 --> 00:04:49.707
-Yeah.
-As long as I know.

81
00:04:49.790 --> 00:04:52.376
[Flyte] Taverner wants them in
lockdown while she sweats Ho.

82
00:04:52.459 --> 00:04:54.336
Let me know if
the CCTV turns up.

83
00:04:58.215 --> 00:04:59.800
[sighs] Where's Shirley Dander?

84
00:05:00.384 --> 00:05:02.303
Ah. I'd check the
downstairs lav.

85
00:05:02.386 --> 00:05:06.223
[sniffs] She'll either be shoveling
one up or curling one out.

86
00:05:07.099 --> 00:05:08.100
Phones.

87
00:05:08.684 --> 00:05:11.311
I gave Shirley some money
to get us all breakfast.

88
00:05:12.229 --> 00:05:13.481
Not you. I'm afraid.

89
00:05:13.564 --> 00:05:15.190
That was before you arrived.

90
00:05:17.234 --> 00:05:18.318
[grunts]

91
00:05:19.903 --> 00:05:21.030
Hey. Where're you going?

92
00:05:21.113 --> 00:05:24.241
[stammers] Well... Talking of
breakfast made me a bit peckish.

93
00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:26.285
There's fresh cake
and crisps downstairs.

94
00:05:26.368 --> 00:05:29.246
[Flyte] Sit down. It sounds
like your breakfast is coming.

95
00:05:29.329 --> 00:05:32.457
-[honking]
-[phone rings]

96
00:05:32.958 --> 00:05:33.959
River?

97
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:37.296
What? I can't hear you.

98
00:05:38.714 --> 00:05:40.274
-Fuck.
-Hey! Watch where you're going!

99
00:05:41.341 --> 00:05:42.802
[Flyte] Come on.
stop playing games.

100
00:05:42.885 --> 00:05:44.011
And give me your phone.

101
00:05:44.094 --> 00:05:45.387
[sighs]

102
00:05:48.140 --> 00:05:50.726
Coe. it's a lockdown.
Give her your phone.

103
00:05:50.809 --> 00:05:52.937
Hand it over. No comms.
this is a lockdown.

104
00:05:53.020 --> 00:05:54.897
-This is a podcast.
-I don't care.

105
00:05:54.980 --> 00:05:57.066
Come on. give her your phone.
otherwise she's gonna call up

106
00:05:57.149 --> 00:05:59.067
the two Dogs that are
in Roddy's office.

107
00:05:59.860 --> 00:06:00.778
Sorry?

108
00:06:00.861 --> 00:06:03.113
I can't hear a fucking
thing. I'll see you in a sec.

109
00:06:04.281 --> 00:06:05.699
Why are you being so helpful?

110
00:06:06.491 --> 00:06:09.245
I was just... Occasionally he's
not really the most responsive.

111
00:06:09.328 --> 00:06:11.831
but don't know why
I bother. Crack on.

112
00:06:11.914 --> 00:06:14.166
[Catherine] You're familiar with
the Slough House brief. I assume?

113
00:06:14.249 --> 00:06:15.251
Mm-hmm.

114
00:06:15.334 --> 00:06:18.587
Well. then you'll know that
some of us have issues.

115
00:06:19.796 --> 00:06:20.965
Get to the point.

116
00:06:21.048 --> 00:06:22.716
Well. it's just that
listening to music...

117
00:06:22.799 --> 00:06:24.051
Podcast.

118
00:06:24.968 --> 00:06:28.805
Listening to music or podcasts has
the effect of calming Mr. Coe down.

119
00:06:29.431 --> 00:06:31.271
What happens if he doesn't
listen to something?

120
00:06:31.934 --> 00:06:34.144
I'm not sure. We've never
prevented him before.

121
00:06:36.772 --> 00:06:38.941
Okay. listen to the
damn music. Whatever.

122
00:06:41.527 --> 00:06:42.611
It's a podcast.

123
00:06:49.159 --> 00:06:50.286
[whimsical music playing]

124
00:06:50.369 --> 00:06:54.122
[huffs] Ain't no prison
built that can hold me.

125
00:06:54.873 --> 00:06:55.874
[huffing]

126
00:06:57.709 --> 00:07:00.170
The only prison I fear is
the prison of the mind.

127
00:07:00.879 --> 00:07:02.673
And I bust out of
that years ago.

128
00:07:03.507 --> 00:07:07.803
I am mythical. historical
and futuristical.

129
00:07:08.595 --> 00:07:13.309
Roddy Ho is merely the latest
incarnation of my most potent energy.

130
00:07:13.392 --> 00:07:14.852
I cannot be created

131
00:07:16.562 --> 00:07:17.563
nor destroyed.

132
00:07:18.605 --> 00:07:20.357
Sir Isaac Newton. motherfuckers.

133
00:07:21.108 --> 00:07:24.570
The only difference between him
and me is I don't believe in laws.

134
00:07:25.988 --> 00:07:27.656
I am the law.

135
00:07:30.868 --> 00:07:32.202
How long has he been doing this?

136
00:07:33.036 --> 00:07:35.080
About 20 minutes straight.

137
00:07:36.039 --> 00:07:37.291
What causes that?

138
00:07:37.374 --> 00:07:40.628
Is that a lack of breastfeeding
or too much breastfeeding?

139
00:07:40.711 --> 00:07:41.837
[agent 1] Hey. come on.

140
00:07:41.920 --> 00:07:44.715
I'm sure the forest animals
that found him did their best.

141
00:07:45.215 --> 00:07:47.176
[Roddy] Alexander the
Great. Genghis Khan...

142
00:07:47.259 --> 00:07:48.969
Uh. what is going on in here?

143
00:07:49.052 --> 00:07:51.263
Why have you pulled
these people off the Hub?

144
00:07:52.055 --> 00:07:53.265
[agent 2] Apologies. ma'am.

145
00:07:53.348 --> 00:07:56.351
His response to the
room has been unusual.

146
00:07:59.605 --> 00:08:00.606
Wow.

147
00:08:05.986 --> 00:08:08.572
-[scoffs]
-[door buzzes. opens]

148
00:08:12.659 --> 00:08:14.578
-Welcome. Clarice.
-No. Roddy.

149
00:08:16.163 --> 00:08:19.166
I'm gonna let you sit here
quietly for five minutes

150
00:08:20.083 --> 00:08:21.752
and think about this room

151
00:08:22.669 --> 00:08:25.923
and all the things that I can make
happen in it if you don't help me.

152
00:08:26.965 --> 00:08:28.717
Okay? See you shortly.

153
00:08:30.219 --> 00:08:31.428
[door buzzes. opens]

154
00:08:32.971 --> 00:08:33.972
[door closes]

155
00:08:41.897 --> 00:08:44.441
[suspenseful music playing]

156
00:08:59.998 --> 00:09:01.124
And who are you?

157
00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:02.918
You fucking first.

158
00:09:04.878 --> 00:09:06.005
Room for a little one?

159
00:09:06.088 --> 00:09:07.631
Don't fucking touch me.

160
00:09:07.714 --> 00:09:09.592
Oh. for fuck's sake.

161
00:09:09.675 --> 00:09:13.012
What. you just walk in
and surrender. did you?

162
00:09:13.095 --> 00:09:15.556
Why didn't you warn me we
were swarming with pricks?

163
00:09:15.639 --> 00:09:16.932
I did. I called you.

164
00:09:17.015 --> 00:09:18.434
[Shirley] The whole of
London is kicking off.

165
00:09:18.517 --> 00:09:19.935
I couldn't hear you.

166
00:09:20.018 --> 00:09:22.729
All right. well I couldn't hear
that you couldn't hear me. could I?

167
00:09:25.524 --> 00:09:28.736
For God's sake. Shirley. You
used my money to buy wine?

168
00:09:28.819 --> 00:09:31.322
Yes. see. what I thought was that there'd
be that much more for the rest of us.

169
00:09:31.405 --> 00:09:34.241
[chuckles] Well. you
can't fault her logic.

170
00:09:34.324 --> 00:09:36.327
You're really gonna
start the day with wine?

171
00:09:36.410 --> 00:09:39.163
It's a bit early for spirits.
but knock yourself out.

172
00:09:39.246 --> 00:09:41.373
[Shirley] I'm telling you. there's
something going on out there.

173
00:09:41.456 --> 00:09:42.458
Total gridlock.

174
00:09:42.541 --> 00:09:46.170
[Jackson] Flyte's up to speed.
Maybe she'll deign to share.

175
00:09:46.253 --> 00:09:48.589
[Flyte] There's been an incident
at some petrol stations.

176
00:09:48.672 --> 00:09:49.840
Three.

177
00:09:50.841 --> 00:09:52.009
What kind of incidents?

178
00:09:52.593 --> 00:09:53.719
It's Park business.

179
00:09:53.802 --> 00:09:57.473
Oh. [stammers] And babysitting
us? Is that Park business as well?

180
00:09:57.556 --> 00:09:58.849
That feels a bit below you.

181
00:09:58.932 --> 00:10:00.267
Number three.

182
00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:03.187
Coe. what is it
that you're saying?

183
00:10:03.270 --> 00:10:04.438
On the list.

184
00:10:05.981 --> 00:10:07.482
That I mentioned.

185
00:10:08.066 --> 00:10:09.068
Previously.

186
00:10:09.151 --> 00:10:11.362
The destabilization strategy.

187
00:10:11.445 --> 00:10:14.031
Was trying to allude to
it rather than mention it

188
00:10:14.114 --> 00:10:16.075
in front of this
unexpected company.

189
00:10:16.158 --> 00:10:18.452
Yeah. well. the main reason not
to mention it in front of everyone

190
00:10:18.535 --> 00:10:21.496
is out of sheer embarrassment
at the bat shit lunacy of it.

191
00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:24.499
Number three is
disrupt the transports.

192
00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:29.296
Um. he thinks sinister forces are
trying to bring down the country.

193
00:10:29.379 --> 00:10:30.631
Yeah. but it's bollocks.

194
00:10:31.715 --> 00:10:32.758
Doesn't make any sense.

195
00:10:33.717 --> 00:10:35.803
I mean... [stammers] ...why
and try disrupt London traffic

196
00:10:35.886 --> 00:10:38.180
when it is already
permanently fucked?

197
00:10:40.390 --> 00:10:41.391
Oh. he's gone back in.

198
00:10:42.184 --> 00:10:46.272
So. is that enough of a pattern for
it to be a destabilization strategy?

199
00:10:46.355 --> 00:10:49.150
It's not. Why did someone
try and kill Roddy?

200
00:10:49.233 --> 00:10:50.651
That's what we should
be worrying about.

201
00:10:50.734 --> 00:10:52.778
And why did they try and
kill him with the same gun

202
00:10:52.861 --> 00:10:55.405
that executed the
Abbotsfield killer?

203
00:10:57.241 --> 00:10:59.117
What? Wait. how'd you know that?

204
00:10:59.618 --> 00:11:00.619
Taverner.

205
00:11:00.702 --> 00:11:02.580
And why are you just
telling us that now?

206
00:11:02.663 --> 00:11:05.624
[sighs] 'Cause
I've been thinking.

207
00:11:05.707 --> 00:11:08.711
Executed? I thought the
Abbotsfield killer killed himself?

208
00:11:08.794 --> 00:11:12.130
[grunts] Taverner used
the word "executed."

209
00:11:13.799 --> 00:11:15.425
And Flyte's not correcting me.

210
00:11:17.511 --> 00:11:18.512
[sighs]

211
00:11:19.096 --> 00:11:20.014
Excuse me?

212
00:11:20.097 --> 00:11:22.933
Couldn't spare me some change. could
you? I'm trying to get a hostel.

213
00:11:24.101 --> 00:11:25.352
Have a nice day.

214
00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:29.648
Bad day?

215
00:11:29.731 --> 00:11:31.400
Every day is bad. mate.

216
00:11:31.483 --> 00:11:32.651
Nobody's got any money.

217
00:11:32.734 --> 00:11:33.736
[person] Yeah.

218
00:11:33.819 --> 00:11:36.113
Hard times all around. eh?

219
00:11:36.196 --> 00:11:38.574
I mean they don't have
any coins or notes.

220
00:11:38.657 --> 00:11:41.577
Pay for everything
on their phones.

221
00:11:41.660 --> 00:11:42.744
[person] Hey.

222
00:11:44.162 --> 00:11:45.622
I got some money for you.

223
00:11:49.209 --> 00:11:51.211
And something I think
you want more than money.

224
00:11:54.631 --> 00:11:55.674
Oh!

225
00:11:56.383 --> 00:11:57.634
Not so fast. bro.

226
00:12:02.973 --> 00:12:05.017
Need you to drop
something off first.

227
00:12:09.897 --> 00:12:12.149
[engines idle in distance]

228
00:12:12.232 --> 00:12:14.067
[sniffs. sighs]

229
00:12:14.776 --> 00:12:16.112
[horns honk]

230
00:12:16.195 --> 00:12:17.279
[sighs]

231
00:12:18.739 --> 00:12:20.950
Sorry about that. [sighs]

232
00:12:21.033 --> 00:12:22.576
About what?

233
00:12:25.662 --> 00:12:26.789
Oh. my God.

234
00:12:26.872 --> 00:12:28.707
-Oh. fuck.
-[all coughing]

235
00:12:28.790 --> 00:12:30.668
Oh. fuck me. That's bad.

236
00:12:30.751 --> 00:12:32.837
I really think you
should see a doctor.

237
00:12:32.920 --> 00:12:34.380
[River] I think you
gave me lung cancer.

238
00:12:34.463 --> 00:12:36.048
[Shirley] Was that a fart?

239
00:12:36.131 --> 00:12:37.425
Yeah. mostly.

240
00:12:37.508 --> 00:12:38.843
I'm not saying I like the sound.

241
00:12:38.926 --> 00:12:40.928
but it does serve as a sort
of early warning system.

242
00:12:41.011 --> 00:12:43.848
Uh. No. stay in the
room! Stay in the room.

