483
00:24:32.848 --> 00:24:35.142
Okay. So. what...
what comes next?

484
00:24:35.225 --> 00:24:36.393
Five.

485
00:24:37.728 --> 00:24:38.813
Yes. I can count.

486
00:24:38.896 --> 00:24:40.397
What is number five?

487
00:24:40.981 --> 00:24:43.108
Assassinate a populist leader.

488
00:24:43.984 --> 00:24:45.344
The mayoral debate's
this evening.

489
00:24:45.903 --> 00:24:49.657
Well. Gimball... G-Gimball's a populist.
What. they're gonna whack Gimball?

490
00:24:49.740 --> 00:24:52.159
Uh. Welles. I need to
speak to the Park urgently.

491
00:24:52.242 --> 00:24:53.786
You don't get to
speak to anyone.

492
00:24:53.869 --> 00:24:56.622
You're on lockdown. remember?
That came from the Park.

493
00:24:57.289 --> 00:24:58.874
Okay. let me call Flyte then.

494
00:24:58.957 --> 00:25:02.420
She told me to not let you communicate
with anyone and to not trust you.

495
00:25:02.503 --> 00:25:04.422
Pretty sure you were
there when she said it

496
00:25:04.505 --> 00:25:05.756
so why would she
want a call from you?

497
00:25:05.839 --> 00:25:08.175
Well. fuck it
then. You call her.

498
00:25:08.926 --> 00:25:12.471
You mistake me for someone who
takes orders rather than gives them.

499
00:25:12.554 --> 00:25:15.682
-Okay. then give her a message.
-What's the message?

500
00:25:16.767 --> 00:25:19.269
Someone is about to try
and kill Dennis Gimball.

501
00:25:20.229 --> 00:25:21.396
Evergreen statement.

502
00:25:22.564 --> 00:25:27.236
Ho. Abbotsfield. The...
The traffic disruption.

503
00:25:27.319 --> 00:25:30.113
Now this fucking
bomb at the zoo.

504
00:25:30.614 --> 00:25:33.993
T-They're all part of a
destabilization strategy.

505
00:25:34.076 --> 00:25:37.705
The next on the list is
assassinate a populist leader.

506
00:25:37.788 --> 00:25:41.792
So right now. we're at DEFCON
shit. fuck. bollocks and scramble.

507
00:25:41.875 --> 00:25:44.169
and the Park don't
even realize it.

508
00:25:46.380 --> 00:25:50.718
I embarrass you. so
you embarrass me.

509
00:25:50.801 --> 00:25:52.386
Is that what you're
going for here?

510
00:25:52.469 --> 00:25:57.183
[scoffs] Fuck. First of all
you didn't embarrass me.

511
00:25:57.266 --> 00:25:59.643
[Devon] I confiscated your
gun. It's humiliating.

512
00:25:59.726 --> 00:26:02.229
So. you try and make me
look like a fucking prick.

513
00:26:02.312 --> 00:26:04.606
Welles. Welles. just
pass on the message.

514
00:26:05.107 --> 00:26:07.568
Seriously. he wouldn't even get up out
of his chair if it wasn't important.

515
00:26:07.651 --> 00:26:11.113
I'm old enough to remember when you
thought Coe's theory was bat shit.

516
00:26:11.196 --> 00:26:12.615
You did.

517
00:26:12.698 --> 00:26:13.866
Yes. but everything you
say sounds bat shit.

518
00:26:13.949 --> 00:26:15.325
It is bat shit.

519
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:17.703
Sit down. old man.

520
00:26:23.584 --> 00:26:24.502
[Jackson sighs]

521
00:26:24.585 --> 00:26:27.004
[mysterious music playing]

522
00:26:37.181 --> 00:26:38.182
[sniffs]

523
00:26:40.017 --> 00:26:41.560
Where is she from?

524
00:26:44.605 --> 00:26:45.939
France.

525
00:26:46.607 --> 00:26:47.608
France?

526
00:26:48.233 --> 00:26:49.234
Are you sure?

527
00:26:50.402 --> 00:26:51.403
No.

528
00:26:51.945 --> 00:26:53.697
I asked her where she was from

529
00:26:53.780 --> 00:26:56.241
and she said. [in French
accent] "lots of places."

530
00:26:57.451 --> 00:26:59.203
[in normal voice] Which I
thought sounded pretty cool.

531
00:26:59.286 --> 00:27:00.788
Might use that line
myself actually.

532
00:27:00.871 --> 00:27:03.582
Why didn't you tell your
coworkers about her?

533
00:27:03.665 --> 00:27:06.085
My last relationship ended
badly. I didn't wanna jinx it.

534
00:27:06.168 --> 00:27:09.296
Well. your last relationship
was with a bot. Roddy.

535
00:27:10.297 --> 00:27:12.967
We think it was profiling
you. identifying weaknesses.

536
00:27:13.050 --> 00:27:15.845
-so that they could manipulate you.
-[scoffs] Okay. yeah.

537
00:27:15.928 --> 00:27:18.764
This all seems very
conspiracy theory. yeah.

538
00:27:18.847 --> 00:27:21.684
So can you just go out there
and get Tara on the phone.

539
00:27:21.767 --> 00:27:24.520
-and we can straighten this all out?
-Her phone's dead.

540
00:27:24.603 --> 00:27:26.856
And she's not at the
address she gave you.

541
00:27:26.939 --> 00:27:29.733
Which she also gave to the events
company she was working for.

542
00:27:29.816 --> 00:27:34.655
In fact. we don't even know
if Tara is her real name.

543
00:27:36.114 --> 00:27:37.991
Why would she give
me a false name?

544
00:27:39.243 --> 00:27:40.244
[sighs]

545
00:27:42.704 --> 00:27:44.122
She was a honey trapper.

546
00:27:45.332 --> 00:27:48.710
She lied to you.
manipulated you.

547
00:27:49.378 --> 00:27:52.422
She's trying to extract
something from you.

548
00:27:52.965 --> 00:27:54.675
Something about Abbotsfield.

549
00:27:55.676 --> 00:27:57.970
[stammers] She
didn't get anything.

550
00:28:00.514 --> 00:28:03.267
That's why they
tried to kill me.

551
00:28:03.350 --> 00:28:07.021
[chuckles] See. this is what
happens when a honey trapper

552
00:28:07.104 --> 00:28:08.689
gets a taste of honey
themselves. you know?

553
00:28:08.772 --> 00:28:11.817
Things. they go loco. Yeah.
I've... I've seen it before.

554
00:28:11.900 --> 00:28:14.737
It was in a Cindy Crawford flick. I
think. She only did a couple of them...

555
00:28:14.820 --> 00:28:16.363
Roddy. you're
fighting reality here.

556
00:28:16.446 --> 00:28:19.992
No. look. It's rule number one:
never fall in love with the target.

557
00:28:20.075 --> 00:28:22.828
But forbidden fruit
always tastes sweeter.

558
00:28:23.787 --> 00:28:25.122
It became a real relationship.

559
00:28:25.205 --> 00:28:27.917
She... She turned against her
handlers. risked everything.

560
00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:32.546
I mean. that's why they tried to take
my life. to punish her and all women.

561
00:28:34.715 --> 00:28:35.883
But mainly her.

562
00:28:39.011 --> 00:28:40.721
[Tyson] The numbers might
be low for the rally.

563
00:28:40.804 --> 00:28:41.931
[Zafar] What? 'Cause
Gimball's not appearing?

564
00:28:42.014 --> 00:28:43.224
Are you saying he's
more of a draw than me?

565
00:28:43.307 --> 00:28:45.225
No. 'Cause the
gridlock's still clearing

566
00:28:45.851 --> 00:28:48.020
and the bomb at the
zoo has people on edge.

567
00:28:48.103 --> 00:28:49.480
Some people are going
to stay at home.

568
00:28:49.563 --> 00:28:50.731
Well. they can't. okay?

569
00:28:50.814 --> 00:28:52.483
I want a full room. I can't
talk to an empty room.

570
00:28:52.566 --> 00:28:54.026
Dad.

571
00:28:54.526 --> 00:28:56.069
Oh. Irfan.

572
00:28:56.612 --> 00:28:57.863
Hey. you changed
your hair again.

573
00:28:57.946 --> 00:29:00.157
Yeah. I wanted it to
be more distinctive.

574
00:29:00.240 --> 00:29:01.283
Hands on your head.

575
00:29:01.366 --> 00:29:03.035
-What's going on?
-Hey. hey. Let go of my son.

576
00:29:03.118 --> 00:29:04.787
[officer] We're arresting
him for breaking into a depot

577
00:29:04.870 --> 00:29:05.996
and sabotaging the fuel supply.

578
00:29:06.079 --> 00:29:08.165
That is absolutely absurd.
What proof do you have?

579
00:29:09.208 --> 00:29:10.918
[officer] He just showed
us his confession.

580
00:29:12.294 --> 00:29:13.921
Oh. Irfan. What have you done?

581
00:29:14.004 --> 00:29:16.548
Unlike you I followed
my conscience.

582
00:29:17.174 --> 00:29:18.426
No. you've done this
to embarrass me.

583
00:29:18.509 --> 00:29:19.802
No. you embarrass me.

584
00:29:19.885 --> 00:29:21.637
Okay? What are you
doing for my generation?

585
00:29:21.720 --> 00:29:23.889
Look. I've told you we can only go
one step at a time on these issues.

586
00:29:23.972 --> 00:29:26.267
No. you're all talk
and no action. Dad.

587
00:29:26.350 --> 00:29:27.518
Okay. there is no time.

588
00:29:27.601 --> 00:29:30.604
The planet is dying
from plastics!

589
00:29:30.687 --> 00:29:33.858
The last thing we need is
another plastic politician!

590
00:29:33.941 --> 00:29:36.610
-You shouldn't be here.
-Plastic politician!

591
00:29:36.693 --> 00:29:39.488
-[bystanders murmur]
-Plastic politician!

592
00:29:39.571 --> 00:29:42.158
[car horns honking]

593
00:29:42.241 --> 00:29:44.576
[siren wailing]

594
00:29:54.795 --> 00:29:58.507
Berlin was the
ultimate lockdown.

595
00:30:01.093 --> 00:30:03.178
Uh. Spooks' Zoo. they called it.

596
00:30:05.013 --> 00:30:06.348
No one ever escaped.

597
00:30:08.559 --> 00:30:10.811
I was a babysitter for fuck-ups.

598
00:30:11.562 --> 00:30:14.815
Much like I am now.
Much like you. Devon.

599
00:30:16.984 --> 00:30:20.487
Except I had some
charm and charisma.

600
00:30:21.613 --> 00:30:23.782
A bit of raw sex
appeal. [chuckles]

601
00:30:25.325 --> 00:30:26.743
Fuck off.

602
00:30:27.870 --> 00:30:29.746
Stasi were the real deal.

603
00:30:30.372 --> 00:30:31.832
Yeah. fucking monsters.

604
00:30:32.374 --> 00:30:34.626
Loved to torture people.
took pride in it.

605
00:30:37.880 --> 00:30:40.007
[sighs] They had no rules.

606
00:30:40.883 --> 00:30:44.553
No conscience. No compassion.

607
00:30:46.638 --> 00:30:48.223
Yeah. they picked
up a joe of mine.

608
00:30:49.183 --> 00:30:50.350
Brought him in.

609
00:30:51.643 --> 00:30:53.813
[sighs] To be honest
with you. I...

610
00:30:53.896 --> 00:30:57.566
I think I'd rather be crucified than
have to go through what he went through.

611
00:30:57.649 --> 00:30:59.568
-[Catherine] Where did you get that?
-Hmm?

612
00:30:59.651 --> 00:31:01.529
-[Catherine sighs]
-[Jackson] No. I found it.

613
00:31:01.612 --> 00:31:03.489
-Nope.
-Come on.

614
00:31:03.572 --> 00:31:05.366
-No.
-Standish. I'm fucking gasping.

615
00:31:05.449 --> 00:31:06.450
It's just the one.

616
00:31:06.533 --> 00:31:07.618
[Catherine] No.

617
00:31:08.285 --> 00:31:09.620
[sighs]

618
00:31:11.121 --> 00:31:12.289
[Catherine scoffs]

619
00:31:12.998 --> 00:31:13.999
[Jackson sighs]

620
00:31:14.082 --> 00:31:16.377
-Hey. you want that? Yeah. [chuckles]
-Yes.

621
00:31:16.460 --> 00:31:20.589
Oh. You could've joined the
Stasi yourself. you know?

622
00:31:20.672 --> 00:31:22.591
Yeah. you'd have
fitted right in.

623
00:31:23.884 --> 00:31:25.469
No mercy.

624
00:31:27.304 --> 00:31:29.097
[sniffs] Inventive. though.

625
00:31:29.723 --> 00:31:31.683
They could turn
anything into a weapon.

626
00:31:32.935 --> 00:31:37.397
Eastern bloc budgets didn't stretch to
blowtorches. so they made their own.

627
00:31:38.357 --> 00:31:40.151
[clicks tongue. sighs]

628
00:31:40.234 --> 00:31:42.110
They got an aerosol can

629
00:31:43.695 --> 00:31:44.905
and a lighter...

630
00:31:45.781 --> 00:31:47.450
[melancholic music playing]

631
00:31:47.533 --> 00:31:50.494
And they burnt all th-the skin
off the soles of his feet.

632
00:31:50.577 --> 00:31:53.247
and then made him
stand for days.

633
00:31:54.706 --> 00:31:56.667
They'd make him
piss into a bottle.

634
00:31:56.750 --> 00:31:58.169
Then. they'd pour
it in his mouth.

635
00:31:58.252 --> 00:32:01.171
and if he didn't swallow it. they'd
beat him around the head with it.

636
00:32:03.090 --> 00:32:04.383
So. three days of this.

637
00:32:04.466 --> 00:32:06.176
he's on the brink of death.

638
00:32:06.802 --> 00:32:11.348
and the Stasi can see that... that his
body would give up before his resolve does.

639
00:32:11.431 --> 00:32:12.891
They'd have happily killed him.

640
00:32:13.684 --> 00:32:17.271
but then they wouldn't have got
what they wanted. which was a name.

641
00:32:17.980 --> 00:32:20.899
Stored in the poor
bastard's battered head.

642
00:32:22.192 --> 00:32:24.403
So. they found
his only weakness.

643
00:32:25.112 --> 00:32:28.448
He had met a woman. a local.

644
00:32:29.658 --> 00:32:30.785
He'd gotten serious.

645
00:32:30.868 --> 00:32:33.996
M-Maybe not love. but the closest
thing a spook can come to it.

646
00:32:34.079 --> 00:32:36.582
It's a fucking
lonely life. Devon.

647
00:32:37.958 --> 00:32:40.377
[sniffs. sighs]
Sometimes you just.

648
00:32:41.587 --> 00:32:44.131
you know. you just grasp
at any spark of perfection.

649
00:32:45.340 --> 00:32:47.217
[sighs] So. I
couldn't blame him.

650
00:32:49.928 --> 00:32:52.139
Yeah. they were shacking up
together in a safe house.

651
00:32:54.099 --> 00:32:55.392
Got sloppy.

652
00:32:58.854 --> 00:33:02.941
Yeah. Anyway. they. uh...
they brought her in.

653
00:33:03.650 --> 00:33:05.194
and they worked her over

654
00:33:05.277 --> 00:33:09.031
in the same room as
him so he could see it.

655
00:33:11.867 --> 00:33:12.910
But even then.

656
00:33:14.536 --> 00:33:15.537
he didn't break.

657
00:33:17.623 --> 00:33:19.875
He-He refused to
give them anything.

658
00:33:22.002 --> 00:33:25.714
Even while they burnt all the skin off
of that beautiful face he loved so much.

659
00:33:27.966 --> 00:33:30.594
Even when they beat her in the
stomach with a fire extinguisher.

660
00:33:30.677 --> 00:33:32.304
Even when she screamed.

661
00:33:33.722 --> 00:33:35.265
[speaks German]

662
00:33:37.309 --> 00:33:38.269
What's that mean?

663
00:33:38.352 --> 00:33:40.312
"I'm pregnant."

664
00:33:40.395 --> 00:33:41.939
[Devon] Fuck.

665
00:33:43.232 --> 00:33:45.776
He begged them to
stop hurting her.

666
00:33:46.443 --> 00:33:48.070
Yeah. he pleaded with them.

667
00:33:49.071 --> 00:33:51.865
[sighs] But he still
wouldn't give them the name.

668
00:33:53.575 --> 00:33:55.244
And it was only when
the screams stopped

669
00:33:55.327 --> 00:33:58.539
and the woman and the baby.
their baby. were dead...

670
00:33:59.081 --> 00:34:00.583
[sighs]

671
00:34:00.666 --> 00:34:02.709
That the Stasi realized...

672
00:34:04.419 --> 00:34:06.797
the only reason he
wouldn't give them the name

673
00:34:06.880 --> 00:34:09.382
was because he didn't
know the fucking name.

674
00:34:14.429 --> 00:34:15.681
Never had.

675
00:34:16.223 --> 00:34:17.850
[Devon] Fucking hell.

676
00:34:18.976 --> 00:34:20.310
And what did they
do to him then?

677
00:34:20.393 --> 00:34:23.230
[breathes deeply]

678
00:34:23.313 --> 00:34:25.065
Oh. he was free to go.

679
00:34:26.900 --> 00:34:28.150
As we are now.

680
00:34:28.860 --> 00:34:29.862
What?

681
00:34:30.987 --> 00:34:32.531
What the fuck are you doing?

682
00:34:33.156 --> 00:34:34.949
[shouting]

683
00:34:37.202 --> 00:34:38.620
[grunts]

684
00:34:39.580 --> 00:34:40.789
[Devon] Fuck.

685
00:34:42.791 --> 00:34:43.750
Shit.

686
00:34:43.833 --> 00:34:45.210
Oh. fuck.

687
00:34:51.007 --> 00:34:53.135
Give me my phone.

688
00:34:57.431 --> 00:34:59.517
[stammers] Fuck me.

689
00:34:59.600 --> 00:35:02.060
You lot were really
paying attention for once.

690
00:35:03.604 --> 00:35:04.605
Hey.

691
00:35:22.289 --> 00:35:23.874
Well. we did ask you nicely.

692
00:35:23.957 --> 00:35:25.418
Fuck you. man.

693
00:35:25.501 --> 00:35:27.044
You'll be thrown out for this.

694
00:35:27.127 --> 00:35:29.171
We've already been thrown out.

695
00:35:29.254 --> 00:35:31.590
-[Devon] Fuck.
-Come on. fuckwits.

696
00:35:32.591 --> 00:35:35.886
Oh. I love that we're still fuckwits even
though we just broke out of lockdown.

697
00:35:36.970 --> 00:35:39.890
Everyone's gonna have to type
those out again when we get back.

698
00:35:40.682 --> 00:35:42.017
-[River] Nope.
-[sighs]

699
00:35:48.065 --> 00:35:49.441
Fuck you.

700
00:36:05.624 --> 00:36:07.251
[car horns honking]

701
00:36:09.461 --> 00:36:10.462
All right.

702
00:36:10.963 --> 00:36:12.381
Everyone off to the debate.

703
00:36:12.464 --> 00:36:15.050
Debate's canceled. They're
holding separate rallies.

704
00:36:15.133 --> 00:36:18.012
[Jackson sighs] Okay.
you go with Cartwright.

705
00:36:18.095 --> 00:36:20.097
Head to Gimball's. He's
the obvious target.

706
00:36:20.180 --> 00:36:22.933
You go to Jaffrey's.
Just as a precaution.

707
00:36:25.811 --> 00:36:27.354
Hey. can I get
one of those guns?

708
00:36:28.021 --> 00:36:30.357
No. you can't. We're gonna
need them more than you.

709
00:36:33.360 --> 00:36:36.238
Lamb. that story. was that you?

710
00:36:36.822 --> 00:36:38.574
Were you the one being tortured?

711
00:36:38.657 --> 00:36:41.368
[scoffs] Don't be
fucking daft. Standish.

712
00:36:41.451 --> 00:36:43.495
I-I made it up.

713
00:36:47.791 --> 00:36:49.627
Uh. well. I'll go
with Shirley then.

714
00:36:49.710 --> 00:36:50.961
[Shirley] Where are you going?

715
00:36:51.044 --> 00:36:52.671
Away from you.

716
00:36:56.383 --> 00:37:00.095
[Diana] <i>Did Tara ever ask you
about any aspect of your work?</i>

717
00:37:00.929 --> 00:37:02.932
[Roddy] <i>Look. if she was ever
tasked with finding anything out.</i>

718
00:37:03.015 --> 00:37:05.809
<i>that went out the window when
she fell for the Hot Rod.</i>

719
00:37:07.019 --> 00:37:08.813
-[Diana] <i>If you are lying...</i>
-[sniffs]

720
00:37:08.896 --> 00:37:14.610
<i>...or even if some tiny little
thing genuinely slipped your mind.</i>

721
00:37:14.693 --> 00:37:18.322
you will be locked away
for a very long time

722
00:37:18.405 --> 00:37:21.742
in a much nastier and
smaller cell than this.

723
00:37:22.910 --> 00:37:26.497
I'm telling you. she had no
interest in me being a spy.

724
00:37:26.580 --> 00:37:28.207
It meant nothing to her.

725
00:37:28.290 --> 00:37:32.128
She wasn't even fussed when I showed
her I could hack into the MI5 database.

726
00:37:32.211 --> 00:37:33.421
[suspenseful music playing]

727
00:37:33.504 --> 00:37:34.588
You did what?

728
00:37:35.464 --> 00:37:37.216
Chill. I was just
trying to impress her.

729
00:37:37.299 --> 00:37:42.054
Sorry. just to be clear. you showed
her how to enter the MI5 database?

730
00:37:42.137 --> 00:37:44.223
Relax. yeah? She
couldn't replicate it.

731
00:37:44.306 --> 00:37:46.141
I've got the fastest
fingers in the West.

732
00:37:46.975 --> 00:37:48.018
You can quote me on that.

733
00:37:48.101 --> 00:37:49.645
And was she ever left alone?

734
00:37:49.728 --> 00:37:51.813
No. Never.

735
00:37:52.898 --> 00:37:55.109
Well. apart from when I went
to get the door for the pizzas.

736
00:37:55.192 --> 00:37:56.902
Like. 20 seconds tops.

737
00:37:57.819 --> 00:38:00.614
-But like I said. she wasn't fussed.
-[door buzzes]

738
00:38:00.697 --> 00:38:03.742
<i>She loves me for who
I am. not what I do.</i>

739
00:38:05.410 --> 00:38:06.703
Did I just hear that right?

740
00:38:07.496 --> 00:38:11.375
He left her on her own with
access to our entire database.

741
00:38:11.458 --> 00:38:14.837
and we have no idea who she is.
what she wants. or what she did.

742
00:38:22.094 --> 00:38:25.389
Find Ho's girlfriend. and tell IT
to check the system for a breach.

743
00:38:27.850 --> 00:38:30.060
["Strange Game" playing]

